As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]]<ref>{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/profile?g=1600000US1700191 |access-date=2022-06-28 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref> there were 75 people, 28 households, and 16 families residing in the CDP. The population density was {{Convert|33.53|PD/sqmi|PD/km2}}. There were 35 housing units at an average density of {{Convert|15.65|/sqmi|/km2}}. The racial makeup of the CDP was 93.33% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 1.33% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.00% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.00% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.00% [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 0.00% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 5.33% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 1.33% of the population.

